hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Definitions and energies for a uniform, degenerate remnant:
   • $N_i = \frac{M}{A\,m_p}$, $N_e = Z\,N_i$, $V=\frac{4\pi}{3}R^3$.  
   • Gravitational energy  
     $$E_G=-\frac{3}{5}\frac{G M^2}{R}
            =-\frac{3}{5}G\,(A\,m_p)^2\,\frac{N_i^2}{R}.$$  
   • Kinetic energy of non-relativistic degenerate electrons  
     $$E_K
       =C_{kin}N_e^{5/3}V^{-2/3}
       =C_{kin}Z^{5/3}N_i^{5/3}\Bigl(\tfrac{4\pi}{3}R^3\Bigr)^{-2/3}
       =K_1\,N_i^{5/3}R^{-2},$$  
     where $K_1=C_{kin}Z^{5/3}(4\pi/3)^{-2/3}$.  
   • Coulomb correction energy  
     $$a_i=(3V/4\pi N_i)^{1/3}=R\,N_i^{-1/3},$$  
     $$E_C=-C_{coul}\frac{(Z e)^2N_i}{a_i}
       =-C_{coul}Z^2e^2\,N_i^{4/3}R^{-1}
       =-B_1\,N_i^{4/3}R^{-1},$$  
     with $B_1=C_{coul}Z^2e^2$.  

2. Total energy  
   $$E_{tot}=K_1N_i^{5/3}R^{-2}-\frac{3}{5}G(A\,m_p)^2N_i^2R^{-1}-B_1N_i^{4/3}R^{-1}.$$

3. Equilibrium $\partial E_{tot}/\partial R=0$ gives  
   $$-2K_1N_i^{5/3}R^{-3}+\Bigl(\frac{3}{5}G(A\,m_p)^2N_i^2+B_1N_i^{4/3}\Bigr)R^{-2}=0$$  
   $$\Longrightarrow R=\frac{2K_1N_i^{5/3}}
                        {\tfrac{3}{5}G(A\,m_p)^2N_i^2 + B_1N_i^{4/3}}
     =\frac{2K_1N_i^{1/3}}
           {\tfrac{3}{5}G(A\,m_p)^2N_i^{2/3}+B_1}.$$

4. Substitute $N_i=M/(A\,m_p)$ so that
   $$R(M)
     =\frac{2K_1(Am_p)^{-1/3}M^{1/3}}
           {\tfrac{3}{5}G(Am_p)^{4/3}M^{2/3}+B_1}.$$

5. Compute
   $$\zeta_{ad}
     =\frac{d\ln R}{d\ln M}
     =\frac{1}{3}-\frac{2/3\,\bigl(\tfrac{3}{5}G(Am_p)^{4/3}M^{2/3}\bigr)}
                    {\tfrac{3}{5}G(Am_p)^{4/3}M^{2/3}+B_1}
     =\frac{B_1-\tfrac{3}{5}G(Am_p)^{4/3}M^{2/3}}
           {3\bigl(\tfrac{3}{5}G(Am_p)^{4/3}M^{2/3}+B_1\bigr)}.$$

